"Remember our definition of sequence convergence: `SeqLim a L` means that for any `Œµ > 0`, there exists an `N` such that for all `n ‚â• N`, we have `|a n - L| < Œµ`. The absolute value here captures the idea that the sequence terms can approach the limit from either direction‚Äîthey might be slightly above L or slightly below L, but either way, they're getting close.\n"
